{"questionId": "d5718376-6a71-41d6-aa0f-411bb7f3bb75_10", "correctAnswer": "7", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute x = 6 into the function", "content": "Replace $x$ with \\$6$ in the expression $g(x) = \\frac{6x - 1}{5}$:<br/><br/>$$g(6) = \\frac{6(6) - 1}{5} = \\frac{36 - 1}{5} = \\frac{35}{5}$$"}, {"title": "Simplify the fraction", "content": "$$\\frac{35}{5} = 7$$<br/><br/>Therefore, $g(6) = 7$."}]}